  "text": "Many mechanisms that underlie the influence of person-groups fit on performance and other work outcomes with one of the possible processes in this relationship is communication, a key process that contributes to group effectiveness (Mesmer-Magnus and DeChurch 2009). Research on group communication patterns mainly investigates how groups communicate when important information is distributed equally, because groups consist of individuals who are attuned and aligned, without dominance and demographic differences. [CITATION_1] ) conclude that communication patterns in groups can influence group performance. The suitability of these person-groups can act as input in the communication process because of their relationship with high-level characteristics [CITATION_2] . H4 = There is an effect of person-groups fit on innovative work behavior",
